The paper deals with multitask learning applied to semantic sequence labeling tasks, which are typically studied in the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of data-dependent conditions on the effectiveness of MTL, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks for the experiments, which is a common technique in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of MTL on image captioning, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
